IPhoneSeries.Description: iPhone XR has a 6.1-inch1 Liquid Retina display. The back is glass, and there's an anodized aluminum band around the frame. The side button is on the right side of the device. There is a 12 MP wide-angle camera on the back.

iPhone XS has a 5.8-inch1 all-screen Super Retina display. The back is glass, and there's a stainless steel band around the frame. The side button is on the right side of the device. There are 12 MP wide-angle and telephoto cameras on the back.

iPhone XS Max has a 6.5-inch1 all-screen Super Retina display. The back is glass, and there's a stainless steel band around the frame. The side button is on the right side of the device. There are 12 MP wide-angle and telephoto cameras on the back.

The iPhone 11 was introduced in September 2019, and Apple has continued selling it at a reduced starting price of $599 following the introduction of the iPhone 12 lineup. The iPhone 11 features a 6.1-inch display, a dual-lens camera, and an A13 Bionic chip.

Originally introduced in September 2019, the iPhone 11 Pro was discontinued following the introduction of the iPhone 12 lineup. The iPhone 11 Pro and iPhone 11 Pro Max offered triple-lens cameras, A13 chips, faster Face ID, Night Mode, shatter-resistant glass.

Apple announced the iPhone 12 at its October 2020 event. The iPhone lineup now has four distinct models, two pro and two non-pro. The long-rumored flagship iPhone has 5G, flat sides, and an improved camera system.

Apple’s iPhone 12 line is totally redesigned and features four models — the iPhone 12 mini, the iPhone 12, the iPhone 12 Pro, and the iPhone 12 Pro Max — at a range of screen sizes and price points. Across the board, Apple’s added new video features, a new MagSafe charging system, the new A14 processor.
